Sentence: This is the fourth line that I have been in.
Ses01F_impro05_F003 [009.2000-013.0200]: I flew in over three hours ago, I've been in four different lines.

They told me to go to the next one.
I waited through that for three planes and now I'm here.
I'm really sorry that you had to do that.

When can I expect my bag here?

Yeah, I don't see- I don't see any--
Ses01F_impro05_M010 [043.8600-049.9700]: I don't see any record of it, and I-usually when I don't see a record of it, that means um-
Ses01F_impro05_M011 [049.9700-070.2600]: we've mistakenly lost your baggage.
On behalf of Jet Blue I would like to apologize for any inconvenience.
I am allowed to issue you a fifty dollar gift card which you can use any future flights you want to take with us.

I'm very sorry, once again...

If it's not here, I'm really sorry there is nothing I can do because...

That's supposed to replace everything that I have?
Do you understand how much I have packed in there?
Not only does it have sentimental value; it can't be replaced like that.
Ses01F_impro05_F016 [118.5300-122.4400]: We flew in from Paris.
I've been shopping for three weeks.

But if you see the sign that's right behind me here, it spells it out really clearly that we are not held liable--
Ses01F_impro05_F017 [127.4850-136.8500]: I don't care what you're freaking sign says.
Somebody- Somebody needs to replace everything I've got there and give me money for my inconvenience.

Calm-

We don't have to do that.

Ses01F_impro05_F021 [155.6000-160.3600]: You are cruising for a bruising.

But right now all I can do--

I feel like I have done the best I could.
